quran[357]{c,v,t}:
  36,28,"After him We did not send down against his people a host from heaven, nor do We send down such hosts"
  36,29,it was but one great blast and they fell down lifeless
  36,30,Alas for human beings! They ridicule every messenger that comes to them
  36,31,Do they not see how many generations We have destroyed before them? Never shall they return to them
  36,32,"All of them, gathered together, will certainly be brought before Us"
  36,33,There is a sign for them in the lifeless earth. We revive it and We produce grain from it of which they eat
  36,34,"We have placed in it gardens of date palms and vines, and caused springs to gush [forth] from it"
  36,35,"so that they may eat its fruit, though it was not their hands that made this. Will they not then be grateful"
  36,36,"Holy is He who created all things in pairs; of what the earth grows, and of themselves, and other things which they do not know"
  36,37,"They have a sign in the night: We withdraw from it the [light of] day -- and they are left in darkness"
  36,38,"The sun, too, follows its determined course laid down for it by the Almighty, the All Knowing"
  36,39,We have ordained phases for the moon until finally it becomes like an old date-stalk
  36,40,"The sun cannot overtake the moon, nor can the night outpace the day: each floats in [its own] orbit"
  36,41,Another sign for them is that We carried their offspring in the laden Ark
  36,42,We have created for them the like of it in which they ride
  36,43,"If it were Our will, We could drown them: then there would be no helper [to hear their cry], nor could they be saved"
  36,44,It is only by Our mercy that they are granted provision for a time
  36,45,"When they are told, \"guard yourselves against what is before you and what is behind you, in order that you may be shown mercy,\" [they turn away]"
  36,46,"Indeed, not one of your Lord's signs comes to them without their turning away from it"
  36,47,"and when they are told, \"Give to others out of what God has provided for you,\" those who are bent on denying the truth say to the believers, \"Why should we feed those whom God could feed if He wanted? You are clearly in error"
  36,48,"They say, \"When will this promise be fulfilled, if you are truthful"
  36,49,"They must be waiting for but one single blast, which will overtake them while they are still disputing"
  36,50,"They will have no time to make a will, nor shall they return to their own people"
  36,51,"The trumpet will be blown and, at once, they will rise up from their graves, and hasten to their Lord"
  36,52,"Woe betide us!\" they will say, \"Who has roused us from our sleep?\" This is what the Lord of Mercy promised: the messengers spoke the truth"
  36,53,"It will be but one blast, and they will all be brought before Us together"
  36,54,On that Day no soul shall suffer the least injustice. You shall be rewarded only according to your deeds
  36,55,The people of Paradise shall be happily occupied on that Day
  36,56,"they and their wives, shall recline on couches in the shade"
  36,57,"They shall have fruits therein, and all that they ask for"
  36,58,"Peace!\" shall be the greeting from the Merciful Lord"
  36,59,"[And God will say], \"Separate yourselves from the righteous this Day, you criminals"
  36,60,"Did I not enjoin you, sons of Adam, not to worship Satan -- for he is your sworn enemy"
  36,61,"but to worship Me? Surely, that is a straight path"
  36,62,Yet he led astray a great multitude of you. Why did you not then understand
  36,63,This is the Hell you were promised
  36,64,Enter it this Day on account of your denial of the truth
  36,65,"Today We shall seal up their mouths and their hands will speak to Us, and their feet will bear witness to their misdeeds"
  36,66,"If it had been Our will, We could have put out their eyes. They would have struggled to find the way, but how could they have seen it"
  36,67,"If it had been Our will, We could have paralysed them where they stood, so that they would not be able to go forward or turn back"
  36,68,"If We extend anyone's life, We reverse his development. Can they not use their reason"
  36,69,We have not taught him any poetry nor would it be fitting for him. This is merely a Reminder and a clear Quran
  36,70,"to warn all who are truly alive, and to justify the word [God's verdict] against the deniers"
  36,71,"Do they not see that, among the things which Our hands have fashioned, We have created for them cattle of which they are the masters"
  36,72,"We have subjected these to them, so that some may be used for riding and some for food"
  36,73,some for milk to drink and some from which other benefits may be received? Will they not be grateful
  36,74,"They have set up other gods besides God, hoping to be helped by them"
  36,75,"but they are not able to help them: rather they will be brought before God as their allied host"
  36,76,Let not their words grieve you. We have knowledge of all that they conceal and all that they reveal
  36,77,"Does not man see that We created him from a drop. Yet there he is, flagrantly contentious"
  36,78,"producing arguments against Us, and forgetting his own creation. He asks, \"Who can give life back to bones after they have rotted away"
  36,79,"Say, \"He who brought them into being in the first instance will give them life again: He has knowledge of every type of creation"
  36,80,He who produces fire for you from green trees and from this you kindle fire
  36,81,"Is He who created the heavens and earth not able to create others like these people? Of course He is! He is indeed the Supreme Creator, the All Knowing"
  36,82,"when He decrees a thing, He need only say, \"Be!\" and it is"
  36,83,So glory be to Him who has control over all things. It is to Him that you will all be brought back
  37,1,"By those [angels] who range themselves in close ranks"
  37,2,"and those who drive away [the wicked] with reproof"
  37,3,and by the reciters of the Reminder
  37,4,your God is One
  37,5,Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything between them; Lord of the Easts
  37,6,We have adorned the lowest heaven with the beauty of the planets
  37,7,and guarded it against all rebellious devils
  37,8,they cannot overhear the Higher Assembly for they are pelted from every side
  37,9,"driven away, and will suffer eternal punishment"
  37,10,"But if anyone does succeed in snatching a glimpse [of such knowledge], he shall be pursued by a piercing flame"
  37,11,"So, ask those who deny the truth if it was harder to create them than all the other things We have created? We created them from sticky clay"
  37,12,No wonder you are surprised as they laugh with scorn
  37,13,"When they are reminded, they do not pay heed"
  37,14,"and whenever they see some sign, they ridicule it"
  37,15,"saying, \"This is plain sorcery"
  37,16,"What! When we have died and become dust and bones, will we be brought back to life again"
  37,17,along with our forefathers
  37,18,"Say, \"Yes indeed, and you will be brought low"
  37,19,There will be but a single blast and then their eyes will open
  37,20,"They will say, \"Woe to us! This is the Day of Reckoning"
  37,21,"[It will be said], \"This is the Day of Judgement which you have been denying"
  37,22,"But We shall say, \"Assemble those who did wrong together with their associates and what they worshipped"
  37,23,"besides God, and lead them to the path of the Fire"
  37,24,and stop them there for questioning
  37,25,But what is the matter with you that you cannot help one another
  37,26,"indeed, on that Day they will surrender themselves"
  37,27,"They will turn upon one another, and question one another"
  37,28,"They will say, \"You used to come at us from the right"
  37,29,"They will say, \"No! It was you who would not believe"
  37,30,we had no power over you; but you yourselves were a rebellious people
  37,31,"But now our Lord's word has come true against us: truly, we are bound to taste [the punishment]"
  37,32,We led you astray as we were ourselves astray
  37,33,On that Day they will all share the punishment
  37,34,that is how We deal with evil-doers
  37,35,"When they were told, \"There is no deity but God,\" they turned away with disdain"
  37,36,"and replied, \"Shall we then give up our deities at the bidding of a mad poet"
  37,37,"Surely, he has brought the truth, confirming those who were sent before"
  37,38,you shall surely taste the painful punishment
  37,39,and be rewarded only according to your deeds
  37,40,But the chosen servants of God
  37,41,shall have a known provision
  37,42,fruits of various kinds; and they shall be honoured
  37,43,in the Gardens of Bliss
  37,44,"seated on couches, facing one another"
  37,45,A drink will be passed round among them from a flowing spring
  37,46,white and delicious to those who drink it
  37,47,causing no headiness or intoxication
  37,48,"With them will be spouses, modest of gaze and beautiful of eye"
  37,49,like closely guarded pearls
  37,50,They will turn to one another with questions
  37,51,"one of them will say, \"I had a friend"
  37,52,"who used to ask, 'Do you really believe that"
  37,53,"after we die and become dust and bones, we shall be brought to judgement"
  37,54,"Then he will say, \"Shall we look for him"
  37,55,Then he will look and see him in the midst of the Fire
  37,56,"He will say, \"By God! You almost brought me to ruin"
  37,57,"If it had not been for the blessing of my Lord, I would also have been taken to Hell"
  37,58,"Then he will say [to his blessed companions], \"Are we not going to die"
  37,59,except for our first death? Are we not going to be punished
  37,60,"Truly, this is a great victory"
  37,61,It is for the like of this that all should strive
  37,62,Is that better by way of hospitality or the Zaqqum tree
  37,63,which We have made as a test for the wrongdoers
  37,64,For it is a tree that springs out of the bottom of Hellfire
  37,65,and its fruits are like devils' heads
  37,66,They will eat from it and fill their bellies with it
  37,67,then in addition to it they shall have a draught of boiling water to drink
  37,68,then surely they shall return to Hell
  37,69,They found their fathers had gone astray
  37,70,so they are rushing to follow in their footsteps
  37,71,And assuredly many of the ancients went astray before them
  37,72,though We had sent warners among them
  37,73,See how those who were warned met their end
  37,74,Not so the chosen servants of God
  37,75,"Noah cried to Us, and how excellent was Our response"
  37,76,We saved him and his people from great distress
  37,77,and We made his offspring the only survivors
  37,78,We left mention of him among later generations
  37,79,Peace be upon Noah among all the peoples
  37,80,That is how We recompense the righteous
  37,81,he was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,82,We drowned the rest
  37,83,Abraham was of the same faith
  37,84,he came to his Lord with a sound heart
  37,85,"Behold!\" he said to his father and to his people, \"What are these that you worship"
  37,86,Would you serve false deities instead of God
  37,87,What do you think of the Lord of the Worlds
  37,88,He looked up at the stars
  37,89,"And said, \"I am sick"
  37,90,so they turned their backs on him and went off
  37,91,"He turned to their gods and said, \"Do you not eat"
  37,92,What is the matter with you that you do not speak
  37,93,"then he turned on them, striking them down with his right hand"
  37,94,His people came rushing towards him
  37,95,"but he said, \"How can you worship things you carve with your own hands"
  37,96,when it is God who has created you and all your handiwork
  37,97,"They said, \"Build a pyre for him and throw him into the blaze"
  37,98,"They wanted to harm him, but We humiliated them all"
  37,99,"He said, \"I will go to my Lord: He is sure to guide me"
  37,100,"Lord, grant me a righteous son"
  37,101,"We gave him the good news that he would have a patient, forbearing son"
  37,102,"And when he reached the age when he could work with him, he said, \"O my son, I have seen in a dream that I am sacrificing you. So tell me what you think of it!\" He replied, \"O my father, do as you are commanded; and God willing, you will find me steadfast"
  37,103,"When they had both submitted to God, and he had laid his son down on his face"
  37,104,"We called out to him, \"Abraham"
  37,105,"you have fulfilled the dream.\" It is thus indeed that We reward those who do good"
  37,106,that surely was a manifest trial
  37,107,We ransomed him with a great sacrifice
  37,108,"and left him thus to be succeeded by a group [of followers] among later generations"
  37,109,Peace and salutation to Abraham
  37,110,That is how We recompense the righteous
  37,111,"truly, he was one of Our faithful servants"
  37,112,"We gave Abraham the good news of Isaac, a prophet and a righteous man"
  37,113,"and blessed him and Isaac too: some of their offspring were good, but some clearly sinned against their souls"
  37,114,We also bestowed Our favour on Moses and Aaron
  37,115,We saved them and their people from great distress
  37,116,"and We helped them, so that they were victorious"
  37,117,and We gave them the Book which helps to make things clear
  37,118,and guided them to the straight path
  37,119,"and We left them thus to be succeeded by a group [of followers] among later generations"
  37,120,Peace be upon Moses and Aaron
  37,121,This is how We reward those who do good
  37,122,truly they were among Our faithful servants
  37,123,Elijah too was one of the messengers
  37,124,"He said to his people, \"Have you no fear [of God]"
  37,125,Do you call on Baal and abandon the Best of Creators
  37,126,God your Lord and Lord of your forefathers
  37,127,"but they rejected him, and thus will certainly be called to account"
  37,128,except the chosen servants of God
  37,129,"We left him thus to be succeeded by a group [of followers] among the following generations"
  37,130,Peace be on Elijah and his people
  37,131,It is thus indeed that We reward those who do good
  37,132,surely he was one of Our believing servants
  37,133,Lot was also one of the messengers
  37,134,We saved him and all his people
  37,135,except for an old woman who stayed behind
  37,136,and We destroyed the rest
  37,137,You pass by their ruins morning
  37,138,"and night: will you not take heed"
  37,139,Jonah too was one of the messengers
  37,140,He fled to the overloaded ship
  37,141,And then they cast lots and he was the one who lost
  37,142,and the fish swallowed him while he was blaming himself
  37,143,Had he not been one of those who acknowledge the glory of God
  37,144,he would certainly have remained inside the fish till the Day of Resurrection
  37,145,"But We caused him to be cast forth on to the beach, sick as he was"
  37,146,and We caused a gourd tree to grow over him
  37,147,We sent him as a messenger to a hundred thousand people or more
  37,148,"and they believed in him: so We let them live in ease for a while"
  37,149,"Now ask them whether your Lord has daughters, whereas they have sons"
  37,150,"Did We create the angels females, to which they were witnesses"
  37,151,No indeed! It is one of their fabrications when they say
  37,152,"God has begotten children.\" They are truly liars"
  37,153,Has He chosen daughters over sons
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How do you form your judgement
  37,155,Will you not then reflect
  37,156,Or have you clear evidence
  37,157,"Then produce your scriptures, if you are telling the truth"
  37,158,"They claim that He has kinship with the jinn, yet the jinn themselves know that they will be produced before Him [for judgement]"
  37,159,God is far above what they attribute to Him
  37,160,but not so the true servants of God
  37,161,neither you nor what you worship
  37,162,can lure away from God any
  37,163,except those who will burn in Hell
  37,164,"[The angels say], \"Every single one of us has his place assigned"
  37,165,we are those who stand ranged in ranks
  37,166,We glorify God
  37,167,They say
  37,168,If we had had with us a Book like that of the people of old
  37,169,we would surely have been God's chosen servants
  37,170,"but they have rejected it, [the Quran] and they shall soon learn"
  37,171,"And surely Our word has gone forth respecting Our servants, the messengers"
  37,172,that it is certainly they who will be helped
  37,173,and that it is Our host that would certainly triumph
  37,174,So turn away from them for a while
  37,175,"Watch them: they will soon see"
  37,176,Do they really wish to hasten Our punishment
  37,177,"When it descends on their courtyards, how terrible that morning will be for those who were warned"
  37,178,So turn away from them for a while
  37,179,"And watch, for they will soon see"
  37,180,"Glory be to your Lord: the Lord of Glory is far above what they attribute to Him"
  37,181,Peace be upon the Messengers
  37,182,"and praise be to God, the Lord of all the Worlds"
  38,1,"Sad. By the Quran, full of admonition"
  38,2,Those who deny the truth are steeped in arrogance and hostility
  38,3,How many generations We have destroyed before them! And they cried out when it was too late to escape
  38,4,"They are surprised that a warner should come to them from among themselves. They say, \"This is a magician, a great liar"
  38,5,Does he make all the deities out to be one God? This is indeed a strange thing
  38,6,"Their leaders departed, saying, \"Walk away! Hold fast to your deities. This is clearly a conspiracy"
  38,7,We have not heard of any such thing in the old religion. This is nothing but a fabrication
  38,8,"Was the message sent only to him out of all of us?\" In fact, they doubt My warning; in fact, they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Do they possess the treasures of the mercy of your Lord, the Mighty, the Great Bestower"
  38,10,"Have they control over heavens and earth and whatever [lies] between them? Then let them climb up to heaven by ropes"
  38,11,"this host too, among other hosts, is bound to suffer defeat"
  38,12,"Before them the people of Noah denied the truth, as did the 'Ad and Pharaoh of the Stakes"
  38,13,"and the tribe of Thamud, and the people of Lot, and the dwellers of the Wood -- these were the confederates"
  38,14,"There was not one of them but treated their messengers as liars, so My punishment rightly overtook them"
  38,15,"they have only to wait for one single blast [of punishment]: it shall not be delayed by one whit"
  38,16,"They say: \"Our Lord! Hasten on for us our fate before the Day of Reckoning"
  38,17,"Bear with their words patiently. Remember Our servant David, a man of strength who always turned to Us"
  38,18,We made the mountains join him in glorifying Us at sunset and sunrise
  38,19,"and the birds, too, in flocks, all turned to Him"
  38,20,"We made his kingdom strong, and bestowed upon him wisdom and sagacity in judgement"
  38,21,Have you heard the story of the disputants who entered his chamber by climbing over the wall
  38,22,"When they reached David, he took fright, but they said, \"Do not be afraid. We are two disputants, one of whom has wronged the other: judge between us fairly, do not be unjust, and guide us to the right path"
  38,23,"This brother of mine has ninety-nine ewes and I have only one. He said, \"Let me have charge of it,\" and got the better of me with his words"
  38,24,"David said, \"He has certainly wronged you by demanding that your ewe be added to his ewes! Thus many partners wrong one another -- [all] save those who believe [in God] and do righteous deeds: but how few are they!\" And [suddenly] David understood that We were only putting him to the test, and so he asked his Lord to forgive him his sins; he fell to his knees, and turned to Him in repentance"
  38,25,"We forgave him his sins. His reward will be nearness to Us, a good place to return to"
  38,26,"We said, \"David, We have given you mastery over the land. Judge fairly between people. Do not follow your desires, lest they divert you from God's path: those who wander from His path will have a severe punishment, because they ignore the Day of Reckoning"
  38,27,"We did not create heaven and earth and all that is between them in vain. That is the opinion of those who deny the truth. Woe betide those who deny the truth, when they are cast into the Fire"
  38,28,shall We treat those who believe and do good works the same as those who spread corruption in the land; shall We treat the pious the same as the wicked
  38,29,"This is a blessed Book which We sent down to you [Muhammad], for people to ponder over its messages, and for those with understanding to take heed"
  38,30,We gave David Solomon. He was an excellent servant who always turned to God
  38,31,"When well-bred horses, which were fleet of foot were paraded before him near the close of day"
  38,32,"he said, \"I have put the love of good things above the remembrance of my Lord,\" until [the sun] disappeared behind its veil and the horses disappeared from sight"
  38,33,"Bring them back to me!\" -- [he said] and began to stroke their legs and their necks"
  38,34,"We tried Solomon by placing upon his throne a [lifeless] body; and thereupon he turned towards Us"
  38,35,"He prayed, \"Lord forgive me! Grant me such power as no one after me will have -- You are the Most Generous Provider"
  38,36,"Then We subjected the wind to his power, so that it blew gently, at his behest, wherever he willed"
  38,37,"and also the jinn, every kind of builder and diver"
  38,38,and others chained in fetters
  38,39,"We said: \"This is Our gift, so give or withhold as you wish without reckoning"
  38,40,"His reward will be nearness to Us, a good place to return to"
  38,41,"Bring to mind Our servant Job who cried to his Lord, \"Satan has afflicted me with distress and suffering"
  38,42,"We said, \"Stamp your foot! Here is cool water for you to wash in and drink"
  38,43,"We restored his family to him, doubling their number as an act of grace from Us, and as a reminder to all who are endowed with insight"
  38,44,"We said to Him, \"Take a handful of twigs in your hand and strike with that but do not break your oath.\" We found him steadfast. What an excellent servant! He turned constantly to his Lord"
  38,45,"Remember Our servants Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob -- possessors of strength and vision"
  38,46,"We chose them for a special [purpose] -- proclaiming the message of the Hereafter"
  38,47,"and, in Our sight they were indeed among the select, the truly good"
  38,48,"Remember [Our servants] Ishmael, Elisha, and Dhu'l-Kifl. Each of them was among the just"
  38,49,This is a Reminder. The righteous shall have a good place to return to
  38,50,the Gardens of eternity with gates thrown wide open to them
  38,51,"They will be comfortably seated; reclining, they will call for abundant fruit and drink"
  38,52,"with them, they will have pure, modest women of an equal age"
  38,53,This is what you were promised on the Day of Reckoning
  38,54,Our provision for you will never be exhausted
  38,55,But the arrogant will have the worst return
  38,56,"they will burn, in Hell, an evil resting place"
  38,57,"all this will be theirs; let them taste it -- a scalding, dark, foul fluid"
  38,58,and other such torments
  38,59,"[And they will say to one another: \"Do you see] this crowd of people rushing headlong to join you?\" \"No welcome to them! Indeed, they are headed for the fire"
  38,60,"They will say to them, \"You are not welcome! It was you who brought this on us, an evil place to stay"
  38,61,"adding, \"Our Lord, give double punishment to those who brought this upon us"
  38,62,"And they will say, \"How is it that we do not see [here any of the] men whom we used to count among the wicked"
  38,63,"[and] whom we made the target of our derision? Or are they here, and our eyes have missed them"
  38,64,All this is certainly true -- the inhabitants of the Fire will blame one another in this way
  38,65,"Say, [Prophet], \"I am only a warner. There is no god but God, the One, the All-Powerful"
  38,66,"Lord of the heavens and earth and everything between them, the Almighty, the Most Forgiving"
  38,67,"Say, \"This is momentous news"
  38,68,yet you ignore it
  38,69,"I had no knowledge of the Exalted Assembly when they argued [against the creation of man]"
  38,70,it has only been revealed to me that I am a plain warner
  38,71,"Your Lord said to the angels, \"I am about to create a human being out of clay"
  38,72,"and when I have formed him fully and breathed My spirit into him, prostrate yourselves before him"
  38,73,"Thereupon the angels prostrated themselves, all of them together"
  38,74,"but not Satan, who was too proud. He became one of those who deny the truth"
  38,75,"God said, \"Satan, what prevented you from prostrating yourself to what I created with My own Hands? Were you overcome by arrogance, or are you of those who think [only] of themselves as exalted"
  38,76,"Satan replied, \"I am better than him. You created me from fire, but You created him from clay"
  38,77,Begone! You are accursed
  38,78,My curse will remain upon you till the Day of Judgement
  38,79,"But Satan said, \"My Lord, grant me respite until the Day of Resurrection"
  38,80,"so He said, \"You are granted respite"
  38,81,till the Appointed Day
  38,82,"He said, \"By Your Honour, I will lead all of them astray"
  38,83,except for those among them who are Your chosen servants
  38,84,"God said, \"This is the truth, I speak only the truth"
  38,85,I will fill up Hell with you and every one of them who follows you
  38,86,"Say, \"I do not ask you for any recompense for this, nor am I a man of false pretentions"
  38,87,this is simply an admonition to mankind
  38,88,you shall before long know its truth
  39,1,"This Book is sent down by God the Mighty, the Wise"
  39,2,"It is We who sent down the Book to you [Prophet] with the Truth, so worship God with your total devotion"
  39,3,"it is to God alone that sincere obedience is due. And those who take other guardians besides Him say, \"We serve them only that they may bring us nearer to God.\" Surely, God will judge between them concerning that wherein they differ. God does not guide anyone who is bent on lying and is a disbelieving liar"
  39,4,"If God had willed to take a son He could have chosen anyone He pleased out of His creation: but Glory be to Him! [He is above such things.] He is God, the One, the Omnipotent"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth for a true purpose; He causes the night to succeed the day and the day to succeed the night; He has subjected the sun and moon, so that they run their courses for an appointed time; He is truly the Mighty, the Forgiving"
  39,6,"He created you from a single soul, then produced its spouse from it, and He has provided for you eight heads of cattle in pairs. He creates you stage by stage in your mothers' wombs in a threefold darkness. Such is God, your Lord. Sovereignty is His. There is no god but Him. So what has made you turn away"
  39,7,"If you are ungrateful, remember that God has no need of you. He is not pleased by ingratitude in His servants; if you are grateful, He is pleased [to see] it in you. No soul shall bear another's burden. You will return to your Lord in the end and He will declare to you what you have done: He knows well what is in the hearts of men"
  39,8,"When man suffers some affliction, he prays to his Lord and turns to Him in penitence, but once he has been granted a favour from God, he forgets the One he had been praying to and sets up rivals to God, to make others stray from His path. Say, \"Enjoy your unbelief for a little while: you will be one of the inmates of the Fire"
  39,9,"Is he who prays devoutly to God in the hours of the night, prostrating himself and standing in prayer, who is ever mindful of the life to come and hopes for the mercy of his Lord [like one who does not]? Say, \"Are those who know equal to those who do not know?\" Truly, only those endowed with understanding will take heed"
  39,10,"Say, \"[God says] O My servants who have believed, fear your Lord. For those who do good in this world will have a good reward -- and God's earth is spacious. Truly, those who persevere patiently will be requited without measure"
  39,11,"Say, \"I have been commanded to serve God, dedicating my worship entirely to Him"
  39,12,I have been commanded to be the first to submit
  39,13,"Say, \"I fear, if I disobey my Lord, the punishment of a Terrible Day"
  39,14,"Say, \"It is God I serve, sincere in my faith in Him alone"
  39,15,"as for yourselves, worship anything you please besides Him!\" Say, \"The real losers will be those who lose themselves and all their kith and kin on the Day of Resurrection. That is the [most] obvious loss"
  39,16,"They will have sheets of fire above them and sheets of fire beneath them.\" That is how God puts fear into the hearts of His servants. Fear me, then, My servants"
  39,17,"There is good news for those who shun the worship of false deities and turn to God, so give good news to My servants"
  39,18,who listen to what is said and follow what is best in it. These are the ones God has guided; these are the people endowed with understanding
  39,19,But what of him against whom the sentence of punishment is justified? Can you rescue one who is already in the Fire
  39,20,"But for those who truly feared their Lord, there will be tall mansions, built up storey upon storey, beneath which there will be rivers flowing. This is God's promise: God never fails in His promise"
  39,21,"Have you not seen that God sends down water from the sky, guides it to form springs in the earth, and then, with it, brings forth vegetation of various colours, which later withers, turns yellow before your eyes, and then He makes it crumble away? There is truly a reminder in this for those who possess understanding"
  39,22,Anyone whose heart God has opened up to Islam possesses a light from his Lord. But woe betide those whose hearts have been hardened against the rememberance of God! Such people are in obvious error
  39,23,"God has sent down the best Message: a Scripture that is consimilar and oft-repeated: that causes the skins of those in awe of their Lord to creep. Then their skins and their hearts soften at the mention of God: such is God's guidance. He bestows it upon whoever He will; but no one can guide those whom God leaves to stray"
  39,24,"What about the one who will have only his bare face to protect him from his terrible punishment on the Day of Resurrection? The evil-doers will be told, \"Taste what you have earned"
  39,25,"Those before them also denied the truth, and the punishment fell on them from where they did not expect"
  39,26,"God gave them a taste of humiliation in the life of this world, but the punishment of the Hereafter is greater, if they only knew it"
  39,27,We have set forth to men all kinds of parables in this Quran so that they may take heed
  39,28,"a Quran in Arabic, free from any ambiguity -- so that people may be mindful"
  39,29,"God sets forth a parable: there are two men -- one belonging to many masters, all disagreeing with one another, and the other belonging entirely to one master: are those two equal in comparison? Praise be to God! But most of them have no knowledge"
  39,30,You will die and they too will die
  39,31,"and, then on the Day of Resurrection you shall place your dispute before your Sustainer"